# =============================================================
# NTFY — ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
# NEVER commit the .env file — only .env.example
# Shared variables (ROOT_DOMAIN, DOCKER_DATA_PATH, TZ)
# come from root .env
#
# Ntfy configuration is handled entirely via environment
# variables in docker-compose.yml.
#
# After starting, create users via the ntfy CLI:
#   docker exec ntfy ntfy user add --role=admin tyler
#   docker exec ntfy ntfy user add family
#
# Access tokens for services (Uptime Kuma, Wazuh etc.):
#   docker exec ntfy ntfy token add tyler
#   Save the token to password manager
# =============================================================
